Photo, Horribly Ever After: This wedding rehearsal may look like your ordinary 
horror show -- but it's for real. Stafford Mills, 26, who plays Frankenstein's 
monster on the Universal Studios Tour, today will wed co-worker Sheila 
Gavarrete, 21, who plays -- that's right -- the Bride of Frankenstein. At first 
they had planned a conventional ceremony, but studio executives -- alert to 
publicity opportunities -- offered to join them in unholy matrimony on the 
studio's back lot where the 1931 version of "Frankenstein" was filmed. The 
bride will wear a dead-snake garter. Fog will swirl, live wolves will bay and 
the groom will be led in on a chain. Said the Rev. Lawrence Keene, shown above 
in the monk's robe and wolf-fur collar he will wear as he performs the ceremony 
from behind a morgue slab: "They'll probably revoke my ordination papers for 
this." ROLANDO OTERO / Los Angeles Times; Photo, (Just for the record, photo at 
right shows the happy couple as they appear when they're off-duty.) 
