<HEADLINE>
<P>
ETHICS HEARINGS AND CRANSTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
During the 1980s I can remember reading about the idolization of Donald Trump, 
Michael Milken, Charles Keating, Ronald Reagan, Neil Bush and countless other 
individuals who robbed and spent our country into a trillion-dollar debt. 
</P>
<P>
Now that we must pay back this huge debt, all of them are pulling out empty 
pockets and pointing their finger at someone else. 
</P>
<P>
I assert that the 1980s can be characterized as the "me" generation and the 
1990s can be characterized as the "not me" generation. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN PECORA, Lake Elsinore 
</P>
</TEXT>
