<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEANE C. DAVIS; ENVIRONMENTAL VERMONT GOVERNOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Deane C. Davis, 90, the former Vermont governor who pushed through legislation 
to protect the state's environment. 
</P>
<P>
A two-term Republican, Davis in 1970 had one of the most successful legislative 
sessions ever enjoyed by a Vermont governor. Legislators enacted a pioneering 
law that controlled major development projects by establishing how they would 
be evaluated; an innovative water quality law, and legislation restructuring 
the government into super-agencies. In April of that year, Davis presided over 
Vermont's first Green-up Day, a project to clean up the state. More than 70,000 
people helped remove 4,000 truckloads of trash from interstate highways. On 
Dec. 8 in Montpelier, Vt., after gallbladder surgery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
