A native of Peabody, Kan., Mrs. Cox began her radio career and moved to Los 
Angeles after her divorce from Morris A. Lawrence. After her marriage to Alan 
B. Cox in 1949, she abandoned her career and began working with women's 
organizations and charities. She was also a founder of Las Comadres Auxiliary 
of Children's Home Society. On Dec. 4 in her Westwood home after a stroke. 
