<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SAN BERNARDINO; 
</P>
<P>
68 MEDICAL RESERVISTS CALLED FOR GULF DUTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sixty-eight medical reservists assigned to the 445th Military Airlift Wing at 
Norton Air Force Base here have been called to duty in Operation Desert Shield, 
the Air Force has announced. 
</P>
<P>
The members of the 42nd Aeromedical Patient Staging Squadron are capable of 
setting up and staffing a 100-bed facility that would provide interim care for 
injured troops before they are taken to hospitals. The group, about equally 
divided between men and women, includes doctors, nurses and medical 
technicians. 
</P>
<P>
Their call-up is expected to last 179 days, beginning last Thursday. They are 
scheduled to depart for the Middle East on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
