<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: MOORPARK; 
</P>
<P>
4 CANDIDATES FILE FOR CITY COUNCIL SEAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GERRY BRAILO SPENCER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Moorpark's special election to fill an empty City Council seat left vacant by 
Paul Lawrason, who in November became the city's first elected mayor, has begun 
to generate interest, with four candidates taking out election papers. 
</P>
<P>
Cheryl Zemont and John Roberts, both former parks and recreation commissioners, 
and Roy Talley Jr., Planning Commission chairman, have declared their 
candidacy. On Thursday, papers were pulled by Paul Childers, a Moorpark 
resident. 
</P>
<P>
The deadline for filing for the vacancy is 5 p.m. Dec. 28 at City Hall. The 
special election will be held on March 5. The winner will fill the last two 
years of Lawrason's term, which will end in November, 1992. GERRY BRAILO 
SPENCER 
</P>
</TEXT>
