<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SACRAMENTO; 
</P>
<P>
POWER FAILURE HALTS FLIGHTS AT AIRPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Commercial flights were halted Friday at Sacramento Metropolitan Airport, where 
an electrical fire knocked out the power and the runways' landing lights. 
</P>
<P>
An airport official said at least 17 commercial flights -- most of them 
intrastate commuter runs -- were halted by the power failure, which followed a 
12:30 a.m. blaze apparently caused by a mechanical failure in the airport's 
elaborate electrical system. Many passengers whose flights were canceled were 
taken by bus to airports in San Francisco or Oakland. Flights at the airport 10 
miles north of Sacramento resumed during the day but were halted again Friday 
evening because the runways' beacons remained dark. 
</P>
</TEXT>
