<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SANTA ANA; 
</P>
<P>
LIFE TERM IMPOSED FOR NIGHT OF VIOLENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A judge sentenced a 21-year-old man to 26 years to life in prison plus a 
separate life term for a night of violence that resulted in the stabbing death 
of a 3-year-old Fullerton girl, the attempted murder of his own mother and a 
knife assault on her boyfriend. Superior Court Judge Richard L. Weatherspoon 
also recommended that Michael Robert Pacewitz serve his sentence at the prison 
mental facility at Vacaville. 
</P>
<P>
Pacewitz called the police last March 3 after fatally stabbing little 
Marcelline Onick 44 times while she slept in the Fullerton apartment where he 
was baby-sitting. Prosecutors contend Pacewitz killed the little girl to get 
back at his mother, Elena Fontaine, who baby-sat the girl and treated her like 
a granddaughter. Hours earlier, Pacewitz stabbed his mother repeatedly at her 
Anaheim home, nearly killing her, and assaulted her boyfriend, prosecutors 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
