<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
REVELERS OFFERED FREE HOLIDAY TOWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FREE HOLIDAY TOWING Free towing is offered to revelers who have had too much 
to drink and want to get their cars home safely. Dates of the service vary. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In an effort to reduce the number of drunken drivers this holiday season, many 
Ventura County towing companies plan to offer free tows to revelers who have 
had too much to drink and wish to get their cars home safely. 
</P>
<P>
The free towing, offered by Towing Operators Working to Eliminate Drunk 
Driving, or TOWED, will be provided to people going home from parties and bars, 
and not to people wanting to go to other parties or bars, campaign coordinator 
Russ Euglow said. Disabled vehicles are also excluded from the TOWED program. 
</P>
<P>
Local towing companies and their counterparts in Santa Barbara and San Luis 
Obispo counties hope drivers will take part in the program rather than 
endangering their lives and the lives of innocent people, Bob Carlson 
Automotive &amp; Towing Manager Joe Bentz said. 
</P>
<P>
Bob Carlson and two other companies will offer free towing to party-goers in 
the Ventura area. 
</P>
<P>
"If they utilize this service and they avoid getting pulled over, they've saved 
themselves $1,225," Bentz said. "That's the minimum fine for first-time 
offenders convicted of driving under the influence in Ventura County." FREE 
HOLIDAY TOWING Free towing is offered to revelers who have had too much to 
drink and want to get their cars home safely. Dates of the service vary. 
</P>
