<P>
Free-agent pitcher Ted Power signed a one-year contract to rejoin the 
Cincinnati Reds after a three-year absence. 
</P>
<P>
Terms were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
The right-hander was 1-3 with a 3.66 earned-run average and seven saves while 
pitching for the Pittsburgh Pirates last season. 
</P>
<P>
The former Dodger split the 1988 season with the Kansas City Royals and Detroit 
Tigers and was with the St. Louis Cardinals in 1989. 
</P>
