<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: JACK CLARK, RED SOX ARE CLOSE TO AGREEMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego Padre first baseman Jack Clark, a new-look free agent, is expected to 
agree to a three-year contract with the Boston Red Sox today that would be 
worth about $9.3 million. 
</P>
<P>
Tom Reich, Clark's agent, and Lou Gorman, Red Sox general manager, have another 
meeting scheduled this afternoon in Boston. 
</P>
<P>
Clark said he believes an accord will be reached. 
</P>
<P>
"He (Reich) didn't say that we have a done deal," Clark said from his Danville, 
Calif., home, "but he said he's real positive we'll get things done. And Tom 
usually doesn't say that unless we're very close." 
</P>
<P>
The stumbling block in the negotiations was the Red Sox's reluctance to 
guarantee the third year of the contract, but the Red Sox acceded Friday to 
Clark's demands. The Padres' last offer to Clark was for one year at $2.5 
million. BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
