</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New McDonnell Douglas Credit Pact: The St. Louis-based defense contractor said 
it has signed a new credit agreement with 21 banks, providing $750 million in 
credit. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement, which replaces a series of expired credit lines that provided 
$710 million in credit, reflects the banks' confidence in the company, 
McDonnell officials said. The agreement is in addition to two other credit 
pacts negotiated earlier this year that provide $1.4 billion in credit. 
McDonnell is among the most heavily indebted firms in the aerospace industry. 
