<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: VISTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An East County man was killed when his heavy-equipment truck ran into a power 
pole Friday in Vista. 
</P>
<P>
Carl Comb, 69, of Harbison Canyon was dead when sheriff's deputies arrived at 
the scene, Sgt. Roy Stamper of the Sheriff's Department said. 
</P>
<P>
About 5,000 homes in the San Marcos area lost power as a result of the 1:45 
p.m. accident, said Fred Vaughn of San Diego Gas &amp; Electric. Power was 
restored later that afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's Department officials said the power pole had toppled over, crushing 
the truck's cab. The cause of the accident is being investigated. 
