<HEADLINE>
<P>
AZTECS HAVE PROVEN THAT THEY ARE WORTHY OF COMMUNITY SUPPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Congratulations to Coach Al Luginbill and the San Diego State Aztecs, who 
proved this season that they are capable of scoring on quality defenses from 
anywhere on the field. I look forward to games at home against Wyoming, BYU, 
Hawaii, Utah, Air Force and Colorado State, who are traditional WAC opponents. 
</P>
<P>
Non-conference foes such as UCLA, Cal, Miami and USC in '92 sweeten our 
schedule in the year to come. 
</P>
<P>
In my way of thinking there is no better way to spend a Saturday evening or 
afternoon than watching the Aztecs at our beautiful San Diego Jack Murphy 
Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
Those in this community who continue to complain about the Aztecs do so from 
the comfort of a chair of inactivity. If they did venture to the Aztec games, 
they would be drowned out by the roar of San Diegans who have found a quality 
team to support. 
</P>
<P>
FRANK A. CUENCA 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
