Los Angeles City 67, Cypress 65 -- Charles Lockard and Eric Pauley each missed 
short jumpers in the final five seconds as Cypress lost in a championship-round 
semifinal game. 
</P>
<P>
L.A. City (9-2) took the lead, 67-65, on a layup by Develle Walker with about a 
minute left. 
</P>
<P>
Lockard finished with a team-high 16 points, Chris Bowen had 15 and Pauley 12. 
Jim Waikle had eight blocks for Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
Cypress (8-5) played without starters Brian Kenney (sore back) and Sam Sabbara 
(twisted ankle) for the third consecutive game. 
</P>
<P>
In the Riverside tournament: 
</P>
