<P>
MAN WITH MULTIPLE SCLEROSIS DROWNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 31-year-old La Habra man with multiple sclerosis drowned Friday in his 
bathtub, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, Jeffrey Dale Irwin, was found by an apartment manager who was 
investigating the sound of running water, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The manager entered the apartment and found Irwin underwater, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Paramedics were called to the apartment complex in the 800 block of West La 
Habra Boulevard, and they pronounced Irwin dead at the scene about noon. 
</P>
<P>
Irwin apparently had recently been diagnosed as suffering from multiple 
sclerosis, a brain or spinal disease, which affects muscle control. He was 
being treated by doctors at UCLA Medical Center and was in the process of 
moving to a nursing home, police said. 
</P>
