<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEW GROUP IS FORMED BY BIRTCHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL FLAGG, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAGUNA NIGUEL 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Birtcher said Friday that it has joined two of the company's development teams 
to form a new group called Birtcher Business Communities, which will acquire 
and develop major real estate projects combining shops, offices and hotels. 
</P>
<P>
The two teams are Birtcher Equities, headed by Baron R. and Brandon R. 
Birtcher, grandsons of the company's founder, and Birtcher Campbell Properties, 
headed by Robert M. Campbell. 
</P>
<P>
The new entity will be responsible for Southern California, Arizona, Nevada, 
Colorado and Texas. 
</P>
<P>
The Laguna Niguel-based developer said the two groups were combined to achieve 
greater efficiencies and not as a result of the real estate slump. 
</P>
<P>
The new group will employ the same number of people -- 75 -- as the old, a 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The new unit will be able to grab a larger piece of local markets and react 
more quickly to business opportunities, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
Birtcher, one of the nation's largest developers, builds offices, warehouses 
and stores across the U.S. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
BIRTCHER BUSINESS COMMUNITIES (COMPANY); WESTERN UNITED STATES -- DEVELOPMENT 
AND REDEVELOPMENT 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
